The paper deals with the anti-Ramsey number, which is a combinatorial parameter studied in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The problem also has applications in interface modelling of wireless networks, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper presents an approximation algorithm for the maximum edge $2$-colouring problem, which is a graph theory problem and hence falls under the category of computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also involves the analysis of algorithms, which is a topic in data structures (cs.DS) and game theory (cs.GT).
